parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal bracket can cause the pedal to stick or detach, leading to loss of throttle control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy
the pedal sticks to the floor
the pedal does not return to its normal position
the pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
smoke and flames are visible under the hood
the speed control system malfunctions
the wiring harness melts
the airbags malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate out of control, resulting in accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates out of control
the accelerator pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to decelerate
the speed control system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, and even fatalities. They can also lead to accidents, especially if the vehicle is in motion when the fire occurs.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
often with no warning signs
while parked or in motion. The fire may start in the engine compartment or spread from there.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain failure can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a rattling or knocking noise from the engine
which can progress to stalling or loss of power. In some cases
the timing chain may break
causing further damage to the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intake manifold failure can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a rattling or knocking noise from the engine
which can progress to stalling or loss of power. In some cases
the intake manifold may crack or break
causing further damage to the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Crankshaft failure can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power
stalling
or difficulty starting. In some cases
the crankshaft may break
causing further damage to the engine.
